      "body" : "Great! Just a nit: According to the [Developer Notes](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/doc/developer-notes.md)\r\n\r\n> If an `if` only has a single-statement `then`-clause, it can appear\r\n    on the same line as the `if`, without braces. In every other case,\r\n    braces are required, and the `then` and `else` clauses must appear\r\n    correctly indented on a new line.\r\n\r\nshouldn't it be written like\r\n\r\n```\r\nif(clientInterface) clientInterface->BannedListChanged();\r\n```\r\nor\r\n```\r\nif(clientInterface) {\r\n    clientInterface->BannedListChanged();\r\n}\r\n```\r\n?",
